COURSE OUTLINE COMPETENCIES (COC) of TESDA CSS NCII 
(Still in improving state...)

In Technical Education and Skills Development Authority (TESDA) Computer Systems Servicing NC II (CSS NC II), 
you need to complete 4 Certificates of Competency (COCs) to earn the National Certificate (NC II).

COCs for CSS NC II

COC 1 – Install and Configure Computer Systems
-Assemble/disassemble computer
-Install operating system and drivers
-Configure BIOS
-Install application software

COC 2 – Set-up Computer Networks
-Create LAN cables (straight-through & crossover)
-Configure router and Wi-Fi
-Set up wireless access point
-Test network connection

COC 3 – Set-up Computer Servers
-Configure server OS
-Create domain and user accounts
-Set up DHCP, DNS, file and printer sharing
-Enable remote desktop

COC 4 – Maintain and Repair Computer Systems and Networks
-Troubleshoot hardware/software issues
-Virus scanning and removal
-Backup and restore systems
-Maintain network and system performance

✔ When you pass all 4 COCs, TESDA will issue the CSS NC II National Certificate.

💡 Tip: Some training centers let you take each COC separately, then once you complete all four, you can apply for the full NC II assessment.

