The actual tasks you do during the TESDA CSS NC II assessment (the practical exam):

During the actual assessment for Computer Systems Servicing NC II (CSS NC II) under the Technical Education and Skills Development Authority (TESDA), 
the assessor will usually give you hands-on practical tasks. These tasks simulate what a real computer technician does in the workplace. 💻🔧

Below are the common practical tasks candidates are asked to perform.

1️⃣ PC Assembly and Disassembly

You may be asked to:
-Identify computer parts (RAM, HDD/SSD, PSU, motherboard, etc.)
-Disassemble a computer system unit
-Assemble the computer correctly
-Connect internal cables (SATA, power connectors)
-Connect external peripherals (monitor, keyboard, mouse)

⚠️ The assessor checks if you follow proper ESD and safety procedures.



2️⃣ Install and Configure Operating System

Typical tasks include:
-Boot using USB installer or DVD
-Install Windows OS or Linux
-Partition the hard drive
-Install device drivers
-Install basic application software (browser, office tools)

You may also be asked to:
-Configure user accounts
-Change system settings



3️⃣ Create and Test Network Cable
-This is a very common task. You may be required to:
-Make a straight-through LAN cable
-Use RJ-45 connectors
-Follow T568A or T568B wiring standard
-Use a crimping tool
-Test the cable using a LAN tester
🔌 The cable must pass the tester to be considered correct.



4️⃣ Setup a Small Network

You might be instructed to:
-Connect 2–3 computers to a switch/router
-Configure IP addresses
-Set subnet mask and gateway
-Test connection using ping command

Example:
ping 192.168.1.2

The assessor checks if the computers can communicate on the network.





5️⃣ Basic Router / Wireless Setup

You may need to:
-Log in to a router admin page
-Configure Wi-Fi SSID
-Set a Wi-Fi password
-Configure DHCP settings


📶 Then test if a device can connect to the network.

6️⃣ Troubleshooting Computer Problems

The assessor may simulate a problem like:

-Computer not booting
-No internet connection
-Driver missing
-Virus infection

You must:
-Identify the problem
-Explain the cause
-Fix the issue


7️⃣ Basic Preventive Maintenance

You may be asked to:
-Clean computer components
-Perform disk cleanup or antivirus scan
-Check cables and connections
-Backup files





✅ Assessment Tips
-Follow ESD safety procedures
-Always explain what you are doing to the assessor
-Check your work before saying you are done
-Be familiar with LAN cable color coding



